task.summary: Default task
Initial Code
Added test cases and replaced old methods to the loft package. Also set up the template package and removed some code that wasn't used anymore.
Started the implementation of the OCR class. Also extended the json file to allow for units. This is currently only working for purification.
The code before the implementation of the automatic OCR Matrix method.
First implementation of the OCR class
Changed the purification.json and added the findHeaderType method. Also added a draft of the refining method.
OCR methods can now detect up to three rows from the two test cases per table. This include refinement methods, filters and the merging of a prefix to a word.
Small changes to the code. The code is now prepared for training on the test data.
First training of the test data. Lots of changes to the json file. Also implemented a couple todos by creating the find table and lowest Y method.
Fixed a bug that made duplicate headers.
The software before cleanup 2.0

The first part of clean-up 2.0. A couple of buggs and todo's are fixed and the code is now modified to make it more Object oriented. The page is split up in tables and the tables are split up in columns. The columns each have their own header, headerType etc.

New version of cleanup 2.0. fixes some bugs and todo's, like swapping I with 1 and see if that equals a number. Also implemented the cell class. System should be ready for pattern and position matching.
Latest version shows the pattern of the table.
The code before the full map Methods.
The first implementation of the map methods and the addition of the scores class. This class will provide better ways to find the ending of a table.
First functional form of Cleanup 2.0 using OCR.
The newest version of the code has roughly 50% coverage on all purification tables. Checked in OCRTest4.
The Code in the first version of Cleanup3.0
The code can now separate the headers from the data per column
The start of T.E.A. 0.4
T.E.A. 0.4 with logger.
T.E.A. 0.4 Trying to be implementable in Linux.
T.E.A. 0.4 with working Linux support!!
The start of TEA 0.5.
Draft of T.E.A. 0.5, including PDF mode and the new REX class.
T.E.A. 0.5 first test of Test1.
T.E.A. 0.5 with configuration option.
Final version of T.E.A. 0.5. For more information on changes, see the Documentation in Dropbox.
First version of T.E.A. 0.6. This includes the fixing of some bugs in the Query mode.
Semi functional version of 0.6 without header detection. Improved table extraction and detection of the data
The column creation works in most cases and the program has been modified for basic column and rowspans. This program is moving to the final version of TEA 0.6.
TEA 0.6 with the first Validation implementation.

Fixed an ongoing bugg that prevented correct rowspan detection and ruined a lot of table extractions. It was fixed in the Table class when filtering on clusters and not adding the line before reseting the breakingLine to Null.
Final (untested) version of TEA 0.6.
Start of TEA 0.7
First setup of TEA 0.7 with a new cell object, improved configuration, frequent cluster bug is solved and improved validation
Fixed two annoying bugs in the clustersize and occurances
First version with indentation detection.
All three clue finders for identifiers and rowspanners are added to the software. Also contains a draft of the header detection.
TEA 0.7 as tested on the new corpus 1.
Improved documentation and provided several toString methods. Also fixed some problems in the validation of the Semantic Framework and the arguments of the constructor.
Improved Header recognition by adding two rules and improved the calculation of the column confidence.
